# Driftara Gallery (`image-scoring-gallery`)

> Stub — the authoritative agent rules live in `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`,
> `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`, `.agent/PROJECT_GUIDE.md`, and
> `docs/CANONICAL_SOURCES.md`. This file exists for Cursor IDE compatibility.

## What this is

Electron + React + Vite desktop viewer for libraries scored by
**Vexlum Scoring** (`image-scoring-backend`).

## Where to look first

- `CLAUDE.md` — orientation and backend integration.
- `AGENTS.md` — MCP servers, slash commands, AST09/AST10.
- `docs/CANONICAL_SOURCES.md` — backend vs gallery authority boundaries.
- `docs/architecture/01-system-overview.md` and `docs/architecture/02-database-design.md`.
- `.agent/PROJECT_GUIDE.md`, `.agent/SAFETY.md`, `.agent/COMMANDS.md`.
- `.cursor/rules/` — focused mdc rules; each is single-purpose.

## Core technologies

- React 19, TypeScript 5.9, Vite 7.
- Electron 40.x.
- **Database access:** PostgreSQL via `pg` (node-postgres) in the **Electron main process** through `electron/db/provider.ts`, OR HTTP to the backend (`electron/apiService.ts`). **Firebird is decommissioned.**
- State: Zustand 5.
- Lists: react-virtuoso.

## Backend integration

- Backend HTTP API on `http://localhost:7860`, discovered via `webui.lock` in the sibling repo (see `electron/apiUrlResolver.ts`).
- Backend owns the REST contract and database schema. The OpenAPI source lives in `image-scoring-backend/docs/reference/api/openapi.yaml`; we mirror types via `npm run generate:api-types`.
- For pipeline phase codes / labels: backend `docs/technical/PIPELINE_TERMINOLOGY.md`.

## Key entry points

- `electron/main.ts` — main-process entry (IPC handlers).
- `electron/preload.ts` — `contextBridge` surface.
- `electron/db.ts` and `electron/db/provider.ts` — DB layer (main process only).
- `electron/apiService.ts` / `electron/apiUrlResolver.ts` — HTTP client + backend discovery.
- `electron/apiTypes.ts` / `electron/api.generated.ts` — API contract types.
- `src/main.tsx` — renderer entry.

## IPC pattern (required)

1. Define handler in `electron/main.ts` via `ipcMain.handle`.
2. Expose in `electron/preload.ts` through `contextBridge`.
3. Type in `src/electron.d.ts`.
4. Call from React via `window.electronAPI`.

**Renderer must NOT do direct DB or filesystem access.** All DB / FS work
happens in the main process behind IPC.

## Commands

- `npm run dev` — full dev (server + Vite + Electron).
- `npm run dev:web` — server + Vite only.
- `npm run build` — production build (electron-packager, Windows).
- `npm run lint` — ESLint.
- `npm run test:run` — Vitest.
- `npm run doctor` — Node + config + sibling backend discovery.
- `npm run generate:api-types` — regenerate types from backend OpenAPI.
- `npx tsc --noEmit` — renderer typecheck.
- `npx tsc -p electron/tsconfig.json --noEmit` — main-process typecheck.

## Regression-sensitive areas

- **RAW / NEF preview** — see `docs/features/implemented/01-nef-raw-fallback.md`.
- **JPEG EXIF orientation** — see `docs/features/implemented/05-jpeg-export-exif-orientation.md` (useMWG: false; `resetExportedJpegExifOrientation` is a separate independent pass — do not collapse).

Changes here require regression checks against those docs.

## Hard rules

- **Never** add renderer-process DB access — IPC/preload only.
- **Never** add new Firebird/`node-firebird` integrations — Firebird is decommissioned.
- **Do not** invent backend API endpoints, payloads, phase codes, or DB columns. Cite `docs/CANONICAL_SOURCES.md` and the backend's `openapi.yaml`.
- **Do not** modify `.git/config` (see below).
- **Do not** commit thumbnails, caches, local-path scratch files, or generated binaries.
- **Backlog contract** — every task starts from the GitHub Project board (https://github.com/users/synthet/projects/1). See `.agent/skills/backlog-queue/SKILL.md`.

## Git configuration — do not modify

Never modify `.git/config` — do not set `extensions.worktreeConfig`, change
`core.repositoryformatversion`, or add any git extensions. Third-party tools
(Gemini Code Assist / Antigravity) use embedded git libraries that fail on
non-standard extensions, breaking workspace resolution. If a worktree is
needed, use a temporary one and clean it up immediately.
